<item>
            <title>[LU-6012] sanity-scrub test_6 test_7 test_8 test_9 test_10a: expected &apos;inconsistent&apos; but got &apos;inconsistent,auto&apos;</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-6012</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;This issue was created by maloo for Andreas Dilger &amp;lt;andreas.dilger@intel.com&amp;gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This issue relates to the following test suite run: &lt;a href=&quot;https://testing.hpdd.intel.com/test_sets/83119ac0-7f6e-11e4-b486-5254006e85c2&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://testing.hpdd.intel.com/test_sets/83119ac0-7f6e-11e4-b486-5254006e85c2&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The sub-test test_6 failed with the following error:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;(4) Expected &apos;inconsistent&apos; on mds1, but got &apos;inconsistent,auto&apos;
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I expect that this is some kind of problem introduced by the landing of change &lt;a href=&quot;http://review.whamcloud.com/12738&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://review.whamcloud.com/12738&lt;/a&gt; &quot;&lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-1453&quot; title=&quot;LFSCK 4: Improve OI scrub trigger strategy: do not trigger urgent OI scrub on the whole system if only few inconsistent OI entries are found&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-1453&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-1453&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; scrub: auto trigger OI scrub more flexible&quot; since the problem appeared for the first time for master on 2014-12-03, the same day that patch landed.  There were a couple of related failures on an earlier version of that patch on 2014-11-17 before it landed.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Info required for matching: sanity-scrub 6&lt;/p&gt;</description>
